            {
              "type": "practice-box",
              "statement": "Calculer $\\lim_{x \\to 0} \\frac{\\sin(5x)}{3x}$.",
              "solution": [
                "On fait apparaître la forme $\\frac{\\sin u}{u}$.",
                "$\\frac{\\sin(5x)}{3x} = \\frac{\\sin(5x)}{5x} \\times \\frac{5}{3}$.",
                "Quand $x \\to 0$, $5x \\to 0$, donc $\\frac{\\sin(5x)}{5x} \\to 1$.",
                "La limite vaut $1 \\times \\frac{5}{3} = \\frac{5}{3}$."
              ]
            }
          ]
